{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"78216a1a-8fff-43fc-823e-999fe060e147","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws<T>` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName);\n}\n```\n\n**Why modernize:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs (e.g., the constructor could throw instead of `CreateUser`).\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call and lets you inspect the exception (message, properties, inner exception).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"76fcbec1-442c-4c78-a9dc-5db58e8daf0d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":246,"requestId":"A042:2FE433:D5FA43:FAB589:69FE8DAC"},"id":"c74d5f60-a8d3-43de-94e3-da446d6d2205","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:28:18.895Z","parentId":"ef9aab7d-2da6-4a96-9b2f-60cd91595992"}
